## Source Document: CM_Cup_2025_RAG_Knowledge.txt

EVENT: Chief Minister’s Cup 2025 (2nd Edition)

OVERVIEW
The 2nd Edition of the Chief Minister’s Cup 2025 is a state-level multi-sport tournament organized to promote sports development from rural to global levels. The event emphasizes mass participation, structured competition, and alignment with National Sports Federation guidelines.

TORCH RALLY (AWARENESS PROGRAM)
Start Date: 08 January 2026
End Date: 17 January 2026
Duration: 10 days
Venues:
- Tennis Complex, LBS (Option-1)
- District Headquarters (Option-2)

TOURNAMENT SCHEDULE BY LEVEL
Grampanchayat Level:
- 17 January to 22 January 2026 (6 days)

Mandal / Urban Local Body (ULB) Level:
- 28 January to 31 January 2026 (4 days)

Assembly Constituency Level:
- 03 February to 07 February 2026 (5 days)

District Level:
- 10 February to 14 February 2026 (5 days)

State Level Competitions:
- 19 February to 26 February 2026 (8 days)
- Conducted at multiple venues across the state

PLAYER CATEGORIES & AGE GROUPS
Competitive Games:
- Sub-Junior
- Junior
- Senior

Recreational Games:
- Children
- Others

Para Games:
- Open Category

ADMINISTRATIVE STRUCTURE
- Each Urban Local Body (ULB) is treated as one unit.
- Each Municipal Corporation Zone is treated as one unit, except GHMC.
- District Collectors are authorized to finalize the number of games and disciplines at GP, Mandal, ULB, Assembly Constituency, and District levels.

APPROVED SPORTS DISCIPLINES
Athletics, Archery, Badminton, Boxing, Swimming, Wrestling, Table Tennis, Lawn Tennis, Weightlifting, Gymnastics, Shooting, Basketball, Handball, Hockey, Football, Volleyball, Kabaddi, Kho-Kho, Sepak Takraw, Chess, Baseball, Netball, Kickboxing, Cycling, Rowing, Squash Racket, Canoeing & Kayaking, Wushu, Atya-Patya, Powerlifting, Softball, Taekwondo, Billiards & Snookers, Judo, Karate, Yoga, Skating, Fencing, Pickle Ball, Sailing, Ball Badminton, Mallakhamb, Para Games, Recreational Games (Children/Others).

CHAMPIONSHIP POINTS SYSTEM

Individual Sports (Athletics, Badminton, Karate, Yoga, Chess):
- 1st Position: 5 points
- 2nd Position: 3 points
- 3rd Position: 2 points

Team Sports (Basketball, Handball, Hockey, Football, Volleyball, Kabaddi, Kho-Kho):
- 1st Position: 10 points
- 2nd Position: 6 points
- 3rd Position: 4 points

GOVERNING COMMITTEE
- Telangana Olympic Association
- Concerned Sports Association President / General Secretary
- Concerned In-charge Coaches

## Source Document: CM_Cup_2025_Special_Officers_RAG_Knowledge.txt

EVENT: Chief Minister’s Cup 2025 – Special Officers & Monitoring Structure

SOURCE CONTEXT
This document is an official proceeding issued by the Vice Chairman & Managing Director,
Sports Authority of Telangana (SATG), Lal Bahadur Stadium, Hyderabad.
It relates to the nomination of Special Officers and Assistants for the 2nd Edition of the
Chief Minister’s Cup 2025, conducted from village level to state level across 33 districts.

ORDER DETAILS
Proceedings Number: SATG/T&S/CM’s Cup 25/696/2025
Order Date: 27 December 2025
Reference: G.O. Rt. No. 391, dated 18.12.2025, Youth Advancement & Culture (Sports) Department, Government of Telangana.

PURPOSE OF NOMINATION
The Government of Telangana accorded permission to conduct the 2nd Edition of the
Chief Minister’s Cup 2025 with the vision:
“Rural to Global – Crafting Champions”.

The Sports Authority of Telangana (SATG) nominated Special Officers and Assistants
for all 33 districts to handle:
- Overall in-charge responsibilities
- Registration
- Monitoring
- Smooth conduct of competitions
- Torch Relay coordination

EVENT DURATION
Chief Minister’s Cup 2025:
- From: 05 January 2026
- To: 24 February 2026
(Including CM’s Cup Torch Relay)

ROLE DEFINITIONS
Special Officer:
- Overall in-charge at district level
- Responsible for coordination, supervision, and execution
- Acts as nodal authority for the district

Assistant Officers / Coaches:
- Support Special Officer
- Handle discipline-specific coordination
- Assist in trials, registrations, and monitoring

DISTRICT-WISE STRUCTURE
Each district in Telangana is assigned:
- One Special Officer
- Multiple Assistant Officers / Coaches
- One District Youth Sports Officer (DYSO) for coordination

AUTHORITY & COMMUNICATION
- Officers function under the administrative control of SATG.
- They are responsible for guiding all concerned stakeholders
  for successful conduct of CM Cup 2025 at village, mandal,
  constituency, district, and state levels.

ISSUING AUTHORITY
Vice Chairman & Managing Director,
Sports Authority of Telangana

RAG USAGE NOTES
- Use this document for governance, officer roles, monitoring structure questions.
- Individual phone numbers are sensitive and should not be exposed in public responses.

## Source Document: Registration Process for Athletes.txt

Registration Process for Athletes

Step 1: Visit the official website: https://satg.telangana.gov.in/ 

Step 2: Click on the "Online Services" tab and select "CM’s CUP" from the dropdown menu. 

Step 3: Click on the "Register" button. 

Step 4: Enter your Mobile Number and the Captcha code displayed on the screen. 

Step 5: Enter the OTP sent to your mobile number.

Detail: The OTP is valid for 10 minutes.

Sample Message: "CMCUP2025 Registration OTP is: 546897. It’s valid for 10 minutes. - CMs CUP 2025 :: TG-SAT (SMS)" 

Step 6: Fill in the Player Details in the registration form and upload the required documents.
